quran[33]{c,v,t}:
  43,24,"He said, \" (Even) if I should come to you with a better guidance than you found your fathers upon?\" They said, \"Surely we are disbelievers in what you have been sent with"
  43,25,Then We took vengeance upon them; so look into how was the end of the beliers
  43,26,"And as Ibrahim (Abraham) said to his father and his people, \"Surely I (myself) am completely quit of whatever you worship"
  43,27,Except Him Who originated me; so surely He will soon guide me
  43,28,And he made it a word enduring among his posterity that possibly they would return
  43,29,"No indeed, (but) I made these and their fathers enjoy (life) until the Truth came to them and an evident Messenger"
  43,30,"And as soon as the Truth came to them, they said, \"This is a sorcery, and surely in it we are disbelievers"
  43,31,"And they have said, \"Had this Qur'an been successively sent down upon a man of eminence in the two towns?\" (Makkah and At-Taif)"
  43,32,"Is it they who divide the mercy of your Lord? We have divided among them their subsistence in the present life (Literally: the lowly life, i.e., the life of this world) and raised some of them above (some) others in degrees, that some of them may take to themselves (some) others in subjection; and the mercy of your Lord is more charitable (i.e., better) than whatever they heap (Literally: gather) together"
  43,33,"And had it not been that mankind would be one nation, We would indeed have made for whomever disbelieve in The All-Merciful roofs of silver to their homes, and stairways whereon they mount"
  43,34,"And (silver) doors to their homes, and settees (of silver) whereon they recline"
  43,35,"And decorations. And, decidedly, as yet, this is only the enjoyment of the present life, and the Hereafter in the Providence of your Lord is for the pious"
  43,36,"And whoever is purblind to the Remembrance of The All-Merciful, We preordain for him a Shaytan (An ever-Vicious (one), i.e., a devil) who (becomes his) comrade"
  43,37,"And surely they indeed bar them from the way, and they reckon that they are right-guided"
  43,38,"Until, when he comes to Us, he says, \"Oh, would that there had been between me and you the distance of the two easts!\" (This is sometimes understood to mean the east and west; or the rising of the sun and moon; or the rising of the sun in summer and winter) Miserable then is the comrade"
  43,39,"And it will never profit you today, as you did injustice, that you are partners in the torment"
  43,40,"Will you (i.e., the Prophet) then make the deaf to hear, or will you guide the blind and him who is in evident error"
  43,41,"So, in case ever We definitely cause you to go away, then surely We will be the Avengers against them"
  43,42,"Or We definitely show you that which We promised them. So, surely We are Supreme Determiners over them"
  43,43,So uphold steadfastly that which has been revealed to you; surely you are upon a straight Path
  43,44,"And surely it is indeed a Remembrance to you and to your people, and surely you (all) will eventually be questioned (about it)"
  43,45,"And ask the ones of Our Messengers We sent before you. Have We made, apart from The All-Merciful, gods to be worshiped"
  43,46,"And indeed We already sent M?asu (Moses) with Our signs to Firaawn (Pharaoh) and his chiefs. So he said, \"Surely I am the Messenger of The Lord of the worlds"
  43,47,"Yet, as soon as he came to them with Our signs, only then did they laugh at them"
  43,48,"And in no way did We show them any sign except that it was greater than its sister sign; and We took (hold) of them with the torment, that possibly they would return"
  43,49,"And they said, \"O you sorcerer, invoke your Lord for us by what He has covenanted in your presence. Surely we (ourselves) will indeed be right-guided"
  43,50,"Yet, as soon as We lifted off them the torment, only then did they breach (their promise)"
  43,51,"And Firaawn (Pharaoh) called out upon his people (and) said, \"O my people, is not the kingdom of Misr (i.e., Egypt) mine, and are not these rivers running from beneath me? Do you not then behold"
  43,52,"Or even am I (not) more charitable (i.e., better) than this (fellow), who is contemptile and almost cannot make (his meaning) evident"
  43,53,"So, had armlets of gold been cast (i.e., bestoned on him) on him, or Angels had come with him in comradeship"
  43,54,"Then he induced levity (i.e., missed his people) on his people, so they obeyed him; surely they were an immoral people"
  43,55,"Then as soon as they provoked Our anger, (Or: behaved foolishly towards Us) We took vengeance on them; so We drowned them all together"
  43,56,So We made them a bygone (precedent) and a similitude to the later (generations)